OmniStudio Data Mapper Extract Examples

Data mapper extract examples demonstrate object relationships, paging with data values, paging with offsets, working with attributes, and relationship notation.

Create a Basic Omnistudio Data Mapper Extract Example:
A data mapper extract accepts an account ID parameter and returns the account name.

Extract Data from Three Related Objects:
Create an Omnistudio Data Mapper Extract for use by a Case-handling OmniScript. The agents who handle Cases can look up an Account, list all the Cases for the Account, and find the Contact for each Case.

Page Through Sorted Data Using Data Values:
Use paging to retrieve a few records at a time based on field values. For example, page through Accounts by Id.

Page Through Sorted Data Using Offsets:
Use paging to retrieve a few records at a time based on OFFSET values. For example, page through Contacts by last name.

Extract Account Attribute Data:
An Omnistudio Data Mapper accepts an Account ID and returns Profile Attribute values for that Account.

Extract Multiple Relationship Levels and Custom Field Values:
Retrieve Contract data that includes the Version (parent) and the name of the user (grandparent) who created the Contract. Use relationship notation with custom fields.

Extract from Multiple Related Custom Objects:
Extract data from three custom fields of the vlocity_cmt__CatalogProductRelationship__c SObject.
